        Example of an ESPD Response - last update 20100419

        * This example illustates how to implement one ESPD Criterion of type General Average Turnover;
        * The example uses a concept requesting the value representing the average turnover of the past three years 
          for a specific EO. The response is served by an authoritative business register via the BRIS platform.
        * All groups and subgroups of questions, as well as the questions themselves have been structured using the class Concept; 
        * The Economic Operator provides no evidences, as the values are taken directly from an official authoritative DataProvider 
        * In this example the value responses have been separated from inside the Concept(s).
        * The Qualified Name (qName) of the concepts are (can be) used to
            1) indicate the semantics of the concept via its namespace URI and element local name
            2) determine what data type the concept has in that namespace        
        * The preferred codelists are the ones published by the Publications Office of the European Union (EU Vocabularies: https://op.europa.eu/en/web/eu-vocabularies/authority-tables             
-->
 
